All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Anime
Defines an Anime object as a fundamental piece of the AnimeLog program.
Anime.Language
Indicates the language used in the anime
AnimeIO
Input Output class for Anime.
BrowseView
Defines the GUI components for viewing media entries
Data
Class representing the whole of user data.
DataIO
Input Output class for user Data.
GUI
Main container for user interface, holding a JMediaTable and several JPanels in a Card Layout
HomeView
Defines the GUI components for the home view, with custom statistics for different Media Types
JMediaTable
Defines a JTable type class specifically for displaying Media.
Manager
Connects actions on the GUI to computations performed and data retrieved from other classes.
Manga
Defines a Manga object as a fundamental part of the log program.
MangaIO
Input Output class for Manga.
Media
Defines a generic Media object with fields that are common between all entry types planned for the log project, including Anime, Manga, etc...
Media.MediaType
Indicates which type of media is involved, useful for when the class isn't visible and certain checks/behaviour need to be involved.
Media.Type
Indicates whether the content is a series, or a special.
NewEntryView
Defines the GUI components for creating a new media entry
OptionsView
Defines the GUI components for changing program settings
Preferences
Container class for preference enums, related to Sorting and Color preferences
Preferences.ColorMethod
Indicates how the data is to be colored, if at all.
Preferences.SortFocus
Indicates whether the data is sorted by title (alphabetical) or by year (numerical).
SortedMediaList
List for storing Media objects in a sorted order, modeled after a LinkedList.
